WEBVTT

00:20.061 --> 00:23.690
King Wapol has returned
to save Drum Kingdom.

00:24.190 --> 00:27.068
The only man
who could've saved this kingdom

00:28.695 --> 00:30.697
blew himself up in front of us.

00:33.700 --> 00:37.244
This kingdom is my birthright.

00:37.245 --> 00:38.997
Mine!

00:42.667 --> 00:46.295
And no one
will ever take it from me again.

00:46.296 --> 00:51.509
There is no throne
fit for a king who abandons his people.

01:15.992 --> 01:17.367
You ate a devil fruit.

01:17.368 --> 01:20.246
My body has become like a factory.

01:20.789 --> 01:26.753
Able to consume,
transform, and combine anything I eat

01:27.420 --> 01:29.422
into anything I want.

01:30.298 --> 01:31.548
You're a monster.

01:31.549 --> 01:34.260
I'm not the only monster here,

01:34.844 --> 01:36.178
Dalton.

01:36.179 --> 01:38.389
I'll show you a monster.

01:49.526 --> 01:51.985
Ah, there he is.

01:51.986 --> 01:54.197
My once loyal beast.

02:02.622 --> 02:06.959
Finally, you show me
the respect I deserve.

02:06.960 --> 02:09.254
You command respect from no one!

02:09.963 --> 02:11.755
Where are your soldiers?

02:11.756 --> 02:17.762
Twenty doctors and two halfwits aren't
enough to put you back on your throne.

02:18.346 --> 02:19.597
Don't fret.

02:21.850 --> 02:24.352
My soldiers weren't being mutinous.

02:27.355 --> 02:29.232
They were just digesting.

02:51.796 --> 02:53.756
A desert lily?

02:54.799 --> 02:57.343
So out of place in the snow.

03:02.056 --> 03:03.433
Miss All Sunday.

03:04.225 --> 03:06.144
So you survived Little Garden.

03:07.061 --> 03:10.607
Hmm. But you're still
a long way from your own castle.

03:12.108 --> 03:14.360
You hound us again and again.

03:14.944 --> 03:17.362
You and Baroque Works
have unfinished business.

03:17.363 --> 03:21.326
Isn't it tiresome
being at the beck and call of a sociopath?

03:23.203 --> 03:25.121
It's like any good partnership.

03:26.581 --> 03:28.750
He's got his agenda, and I've got mine.

03:30.126 --> 03:32.378
Sometimes, like now,

03:33.671 --> 03:34.756
they overlap.

03:36.049 --> 03:37.884
I wonder who's right about you.

03:38.551 --> 03:41.136
Him… or me.

03:41.137 --> 03:42.764
You can try and kill me,

03:43.598 --> 03:45.515
but I will not go down without a fight.

03:45.516 --> 03:47.435
That's what intrigues me about you.

03:48.686 --> 03:52.899
You should know that Mr. 0
gave Wapol his very own devil fruit.

03:54.651 --> 03:57.362
The Munch Munch Fruit, to be precise.

03:58.488 --> 04:00.907
And now he's on his way
to reclaim his throne.

04:01.407 --> 04:02.951
Why are you telling me this?

04:04.911 --> 04:07.120
Because I wonder
if you and the Straw Hats can stop him.

04:07.121 --> 04:08.915
This is not a game.

04:10.375 --> 04:13.335
And it is not their fight.
They are just helping.

04:13.336 --> 04:15.797
Come now, Princess.

04:16.464 --> 04:18.340
Like any good leader,
like any strong woman,

04:18.341 --> 04:22.053
you are going to try and shield others
and blame yourself for this.

04:22.804 --> 04:24.472
And I'm here to tell you,

04:25.556 --> 04:26.641
you should.

04:28.601 --> 04:32.396
As you watch your friends die,
do so with the knowledge

04:32.397 --> 04:35.692
that the same fate
shall befall the people of Alabasta.

04:37.610 --> 04:39.529
And it is all your fault.

04:43.783 --> 04:45.827
I almost forgot.

04:46.327 --> 04:50.123
You're going to love
what he did with his army.

04:52.583 --> 04:53.710
Zoro?

05:20.403 --> 05:21.486
Shit.

05:21.487 --> 05:23.531
Usopp! Zoro!

05:24.574 --> 05:25.991
We've got trouble.

05:25.992 --> 05:27.409
King Wapol's returned.

05:27.410 --> 05:30.245
He's heading to the castle.
And he's got a devil fruit.

05:30.246 --> 05:33.498
That would explain the army of monsters
marching towards the village right now.

05:33.499 --> 05:34.624
Where's Dalton?

05:34.625 --> 05:37.295
He went down to investigate.
He hasn't been back.

05:38.671 --> 05:41.298
- Those things must have got him.
- We need to get Luffy.

05:41.299 --> 05:43.967
Dalton told me to protect the town.
It's got to be you, Usopp.

05:43.968 --> 05:46.387
- Ooh…
- No. I'll go.

05:47.305 --> 05:49.140
I've seen what you both are capable of.

05:49.640 --> 05:52.810
The villagers need Captain Usopp
and Mr. Bushido.

05:54.687 --> 05:57.148
- I'll go get Luffy.
- How are you gonna make it in time?

06:00.234 --> 06:01.486
I can help with that.

06:02.862 --> 06:04.947
I figured
something like this would happen.

06:05.448 --> 06:08.575
And since the path is too long to follow
and none of us are as strong as Luffy,

06:08.576 --> 06:10.328
we need a plan B.

06:11.204 --> 06:12.329
Have you tested it yet?

06:12.330 --> 06:14.916
Just finished it, so no.

06:15.666 --> 06:16.667
Okay.

06:19.045 --> 06:20.338
How does it work?

06:20.838 --> 06:23.131
Okay, the launching mechanism is here.

06:23.132 --> 06:26.134
The grappling hook will then
latch onto the cable in the spool here,

06:26.135 --> 06:27.220
and it'll pull you up.

06:27.720 --> 06:31.264
It's not enough to make it in one shot,
so find your footing, reload,

06:31.265 --> 06:33.016
and keep firing until you reach the top.

06:33.017 --> 06:33.893
Okay.

06:38.022 --> 06:39.399
- Hold on!
- How fast will it…

06:42.443 --> 06:44.487
Well done, Princess.

06:47.490 --> 06:48.741
She'll be fine.

07:15.977 --> 07:17.478
Always trying to impress me.

07:17.979 --> 07:19.063
I'm trying to help you.

07:20.106 --> 07:22.899
You're really worried, huh?

07:22.900 --> 07:24.901
I… I'm feeling better, I promise.

07:24.902 --> 07:27.071
Yeah, well, I'll feel better
when you get out of bed.

07:29.365 --> 07:31.825
- How does it taste?
- Mmm.

07:31.826 --> 07:33.953
I've added some more flavor
now you can taste again.

07:34.620 --> 07:36.246
- This is great.
- Yeah.

07:36.247 --> 07:37.206
Zeff taught you well.

07:38.374 --> 07:41.334
Well, you know, the old man
gave me a trick here and there.

07:41.335 --> 07:44.255
Though he'd never hear me say that.
But, um,

07:45.381 --> 07:46.757
I'm self-taught.

07:47.842 --> 07:48.843
Through and through.

07:51.220 --> 07:52.263
Started with my mum.

07:53.264 --> 07:54.599
You would cook with your mom?

07:55.183 --> 07:56.517
Uh, not with her.

07:57.351 --> 07:58.186
For her.

07:59.687 --> 08:02.981
My mum was really sick when I was
growing up. And I was really little.

08:02.982 --> 08:04.901
I just wanted to make her feel better, and

08:05.985 --> 08:08.154
cooking was a way
I could show my love for her.

08:10.907 --> 08:12.325
Didn't start off great.

08:14.243 --> 08:15.827
I used to make her these lunches

08:15.828 --> 08:18.789
with just anything I could find
lying around the kitchen.

08:20.708 --> 08:22.543
Mushy banana amuse-bouche.

08:23.628 --> 08:25.338
Old fish heads with undercooked rice.

08:27.632 --> 08:29.509
It was a real smorgasbord of sick.

08:30.426 --> 08:32.345
And I would march down the hallway,

08:33.346 --> 08:34.889
head held all high.

08:35.723 --> 08:38.851
Nurse's face would turn green
whenever I walked in the room.

08:39.602 --> 08:40.853
But not my mum.

08:43.022 --> 08:46.108
You wouldn't be able to tell she was sick
from the way she looked at me.

08:47.109 --> 08:49.320
Ray of sunshine emanating from that bed.

08:55.993 --> 08:57.245
She'd always go,

08:58.913 --> 09:01.707
"Oh, my little prince,
what have you brought for me today?"

09:04.585 --> 09:07.255
She used to look at the lunchbox…

09:09.799 --> 09:11.551
and she'd just take a bite,

09:13.094 --> 09:14.470
and she'd smile.

09:16.639 --> 09:19.432
Made me feel
like I was really helping, you know?

09:19.433 --> 09:20.892
And then I got better.

09:20.893 --> 09:25.481
Honing my skills, my flavor profiles,
my savory combinations.

09:27.525 --> 09:30.236
But while I was getting better,
she was getting worse.

09:33.322 --> 09:36.116
And every time she'd finish her lunch,
I'd hug her so tight

09:36.117 --> 09:37.618
it probably took her breath away.

09:48.462 --> 09:51.924
And then came the day where
I didn't have to make any more lunches.

09:58.431 --> 09:59.473
So…

10:00.808 --> 10:02.351
every meal I make…

10:05.688 --> 10:07.106
I'm making for her.

10:12.903 --> 10:14.030
Sanji, I…

10:14.822 --> 10:16.323
- I…
- Hey, you guys!

10:16.324 --> 10:17.742
Vivi's here!

10:25.082 --> 10:27.835
Huh.

10:29.420 --> 10:31.756
That's why I'm here.

10:32.757 --> 10:34.466
Wapol won't be far behind.

10:34.467 --> 10:37.637
Surprised a scrawny thing like you
managed to get all the way up here.

10:38.554 --> 10:39.929
It's what needed to be done.

10:39.930 --> 10:41.390
That's our Vivi.

10:43.059 --> 10:45.686
So this king guy is coming after us.

10:46.187 --> 10:48.605
And now he has devil fruit powers?

10:48.606 --> 10:51.107
I guess those Baroque Works agents
really weren't kidding

10:51.108 --> 10:52.860
when they said they wouldn't leave us be.

10:56.947 --> 10:57.948
Okay.

10:58.949 --> 10:59.991
I'll kick his ass.

10:59.992 --> 11:01.076
Hmm.

11:01.077 --> 11:03.203
We need to get down the mountain
and help the others.

11:03.204 --> 11:05.580
Oh yeah.
We're going down the mountain, all right,

11:05.581 --> 11:07.124
but not for a fight.

11:08.376 --> 11:10.293
We're going back into hiding.

11:10.294 --> 11:11.462
You're running away?

11:11.962 --> 11:14.214
Just use your witch magic powers
and fight.

11:14.215 --> 11:16.591
You want to rumble?

11:16.592 --> 11:17.843
Good on you.

11:18.469 --> 11:21.805
I watched Wapol
terrorize this country for years.

11:21.806 --> 11:23.473
He was a piece of shit before.

11:23.474 --> 11:25.351
Now he has a devil fruit?

11:25.851 --> 11:28.479
I'm not sticking around
to see what new horrors he brings.

11:29.480 --> 11:32.608
Pack up quick, Chopper.
We'll take one of the secret passageways.

11:33.109 --> 11:34.527
We can't leave.

11:35.569 --> 11:38.697
If there's gonna be a battle,
people are gonna get hurt.

11:38.698 --> 11:40.448
We have to stay and help them.

11:40.449 --> 11:43.827
Help them?
The people that called you a monster.

11:43.828 --> 11:46.622
The people who shot at you.
You want to help them?

11:47.623 --> 11:51.210
Yes, because that's what a doctor does.

11:56.382 --> 11:57.842
Have fun dying, kid.

12:09.186 --> 12:11.439
Okay. And we're going to get Nami.

12:12.398 --> 12:13.941
Is she… she doing better?

12:14.859 --> 12:17.485
All thanks to this little guy right here.

12:17.486 --> 12:18.653
Well, almost.

12:18.654 --> 12:20.572
Her treatment isn't finished.

12:20.573 --> 12:23.783
I can transfer her to a walking IV
so we can move her.

12:23.784 --> 12:26.287
All right! Then let's go back
down the mountain.

12:27.747 --> 12:29.039
You good with that, Vivi?

12:29.540 --> 12:32.751
I'll be fine. I'll warm myself up
while you get Nami sorted.

12:32.752 --> 12:34.628
- All right, Chopper. Let's go.
- Right!

12:41.343 --> 12:42.595
We'll hold them off.

12:43.596 --> 12:46.014
Take what you need
and find a safe place to shelter.

12:46.015 --> 12:48.392
This way. Hurry. Hurry up.

12:49.518 --> 12:51.145
- Here.
- Come on.

12:53.856 --> 12:54.732
Hurry!

13:00.696 --> 13:02.364
Maybe I should go with them.

13:03.532 --> 13:05.576
In case they need my protection, you know?

13:06.076 --> 13:09.163
What's an army of monsters
to the hero of Little Garden?

13:15.878 --> 13:18.088
Not my problem.

13:22.218 --> 13:23.302
Ah.

13:50.538 --> 13:51.539
Hey!

13:55.918 --> 13:57.670
Where do you think you're going?

13:58.796 --> 13:59.839
To fight.

14:00.339 --> 14:02.424
Huh. What a hero.

14:02.925 --> 14:05.134
I'm sure the townsfolk will be thrilled

14:05.135 --> 14:09.223
to have a shuffling corpse arrive
just in time to die alongside them.

14:15.604 --> 14:16.981
When does a man die?

14:26.490 --> 14:28.241
You don't get to say those words.

14:28.242 --> 14:33.914
His blood is on your hands,
and I will not let you tarnish his memory.

14:34.498 --> 14:36.250
This country is sick.

14:37.001 --> 14:38.669
You and I both know that.

14:39.920 --> 14:41.422
Dr. Hiriluk knew it too.

14:43.591 --> 14:45.384
He wanted to heal this land,

14:45.926 --> 14:47.428
and I let him die.

14:49.096 --> 14:50.973
For that, I am truly sorry.

14:53.350 --> 14:55.686
But I cannot make the same mistake again.

14:56.437 --> 15:00.441
I can't let anyone else die
because of that tyrant Wapol.

15:02.693 --> 15:05.988
This is our last chance to be free of him.

15:08.824 --> 15:10.659
If we don't stand up now,

15:11.660 --> 15:13.495
we will forever be under his heel.

15:15.956 --> 15:17.249
I'm gonna fight,

15:17.958 --> 15:19.418
whatever the cost,

15:20.711 --> 15:22.922
with or without your help.

15:34.308 --> 15:35.392
Screw it.

15:40.189 --> 15:41.357
You overdid it.

15:44.944 --> 15:46.236
I'll bill you later.

15:50.950 --> 15:53.702
We have to hurry.
Wapol could be at the village by now.

15:54.203 --> 15:57.373
- What's this?
- I grabbed all the food I could find.

15:57.873 --> 16:00.208
No sense letting it go to waste here.

16:00.209 --> 16:01.543
Is this Nami's coat?

16:02.461 --> 16:05.797
Yeah. You reminded me
of how cold it is outside.

16:05.798 --> 16:08.675
I couldn't find mine,
so I'm borrowing hers.

16:08.676 --> 16:10.885
She is going to kill you if you damage it.

16:10.886 --> 16:13.055
Relax. What's gonna happen?

16:22.231 --> 16:24.608
Well, well, well.

16:25.776 --> 16:28.696
Princess Vivi

16:29.321 --> 16:32.616
of Alabasta.

16:33.117 --> 16:34.159
Who's this guy?

16:35.202 --> 16:36.036
Wapol.

16:37.746 --> 16:40.124
King Wapol!

16:40.749 --> 16:44.794
And captain of the Bliking Pirates.

16:44.795 --> 16:49.633
And I have returned to claim what is mine!

16:50.467 --> 16:54.178
You've pissed off
a lot of powerful people, Princess.

16:54.179 --> 16:55.764
What the hell is he doing?

16:58.308 --> 16:59.476
Stretching.

17:00.352 --> 17:02.938
With everything you're saying,

17:04.273 --> 17:06.232
it sounds like
we're gonna get into a fight.

17:06.233 --> 17:07.984
You don't wanna fight me, punk.

17:07.985 --> 17:11.654
I eat pretzel sticks like you
for breakfast!

17:11.655 --> 17:13.490
Well…

17:16.285 --> 17:18.286
…then let's hope you're hungry.

17:18.287 --> 17:19.538
Luffy, wait.

17:20.247 --> 17:21.581
It's my turn.

17:21.582 --> 17:24.418
Your turn for what, exactly?

17:25.127 --> 17:30.840
You're still the same scared little girl
from all those years ago.

17:30.841 --> 17:32.217
No fight.

17:32.718 --> 17:34.053
No bravery.

17:34.678 --> 17:37.889
And it's that lack of a spine

17:37.890 --> 17:40.975
that's gonna get you killed

17:40.976 --> 17:44.479
and anyone else who stands in my way

17:44.480 --> 17:48.358
because that, dear Princess,

17:48.859 --> 17:52.029
is the sign of a true

17:52.946 --> 17:54.114
king!

17:54.823 --> 17:57.867
Something your fool of a father

17:57.868 --> 18:00.120
never understood.

18:02.581 --> 18:04.083
A king is but a man.

18:04.833 --> 18:06.585
And a crown, it's just a hat.

18:08.295 --> 18:10.546
The suffering of your people

18:10.547 --> 18:14.134
shows you know nothing
about what it means to lead.

18:15.427 --> 18:17.096
My father does.

18:17.763 --> 18:19.931
Baroque Works will not break him.

18:19.932 --> 18:23.852
And you will not break me.

18:24.520 --> 18:26.772
There is a time for diplomacy.

18:27.648 --> 18:28.649
But now,

18:29.525 --> 18:30.983
it's a time for action.

18:30.984 --> 18:34.153
And I, Nefertari Vivi,

18:34.154 --> 18:37.281
daughter of Nefertari Cobra,

18:37.282 --> 18:39.535
am no coward!

18:49.211 --> 18:50.379
Well,

18:52.047 --> 18:55.384
if it's action you want, Princess…

18:59.638 --> 19:01.722
allow me to oblige!

19:01.723 --> 19:03.559
Aah!

19:06.145 --> 19:07.938
Nice speech, Vivi.

19:09.690 --> 19:10.858
Now's my turn.

19:13.902 --> 19:15.529
Looks like it's just you and me.

19:16.029 --> 19:17.281
Not quite.

19:24.288 --> 19:26.498
Wapol may have taken our army,

19:27.082 --> 19:29.543
but that doesn't mean we're helpless.

19:30.127 --> 19:32.086
He didn't just take your army.

19:32.087 --> 19:35.716
He ate your army.
And he spit 'em back out looking like--

19:46.476 --> 19:47.436
Monsters.

20:03.869 --> 20:05.662
Nothing a sword can't fix.

20:07.122 --> 20:08.706
Take cover!

20:08.707 --> 20:10.459
No!

20:18.050 --> 20:19.176
Take cover!

20:29.519 --> 20:30.687
Hey, ugly!

20:37.527 --> 20:38.987
Sure Kill Firestar!

20:47.287 --> 20:49.122
Maybe he didn't hear me say "Sure Kill."

21:11.395 --> 21:14.398
- These guys won't go down!
- Gotta keep fighting until they do.

21:25.450 --> 21:27.410
Wapol's back!
We're gonna get you out of here.

21:27.411 --> 21:28.953
What's going on? Is Vivi okay?

21:28.954 --> 21:32.915
- She's fine. We're gonna take you to her.
- Keep her still. I have to change her IV.

21:32.916 --> 21:34.458
- You're gonna bruise her!
- You guys!

21:34.459 --> 21:37.087
- Which of us is a doctor?
- Did you say doctor or dinner?

21:53.145 --> 21:57.441
Stop being so stubborn
and let me do my job!

21:58.442 --> 21:59.985
Sanji, I think you should listen to him.

22:04.406 --> 22:07.326
- Oh shit.
- What the hell is that thing?

22:08.160 --> 22:11.747
Whatever it is,
let's kill it and find the doctor.

22:15.917 --> 22:17.710
What the hell is going on?

22:17.711 --> 22:20.379
Baroque Works sent
a super-powered king after us.

22:20.380 --> 22:22.214
And those are his henchmen.

22:22.215 --> 22:25.551
But it's okay 'cause we're not gonna
let them get to you or anyone else.

22:25.552 --> 22:28.722
You stay here.
Keep your head down and your IV in.

22:29.765 --> 22:32.141
All right, Chopper. Time to be monsters.

22:32.142 --> 22:32.976
Yeah!

22:53.830 --> 22:54.664
Ah!

23:03.173 --> 23:04.299
- Whoa!
- Ah!

23:42.462 --> 23:44.714
Whoa!

23:45.632 --> 23:47.342
Oh man.

23:48.218 --> 23:50.137
Hopefully, Nami won't notice.

23:52.431 --> 23:54.141
Can you take this seriously?!

23:55.517 --> 23:57.519
I'm trying to kill you!

24:01.189 --> 24:03.108
You'll pay for that!

24:14.369 --> 24:15.579
Snow Splitter!

24:55.744 --> 24:57.411
Did he just rip his hair out?

24:57.412 --> 24:59.331
- Mm-hmm.
- Okay.

25:20.560 --> 25:22.228
What the hell is this?

25:22.229 --> 25:24.897
The static cling from my Afro
makes it super-adhesive.

25:24.898 --> 25:26.441
Get it off me!

25:29.611 --> 25:31.655
So much for your fancy footwork.

25:48.004 --> 25:49.297
These guys are unstoppable!

25:51.299 --> 25:54.678
- Thought you were the Lord of Destruction.
- Yeah, and we're getting destroyed!

26:15.657 --> 26:16.658
Dalton!

26:19.536 --> 26:20.996
He's got a devil fruit?

26:21.496 --> 26:23.373
Does everybody have devil fruits now?

26:29.921 --> 26:34.175
Let's see what a devil fruit user
tastes like.

26:57.282 --> 26:59.743
Chopper, I could use
a little bit of help over here!

27:00.994 --> 27:02.787
I'm a little busy myself right now!

27:03.371 --> 27:04.705
Not for long, you freak.

27:04.706 --> 27:07.708
My name is Tony Tony Chopper,

27:07.709 --> 27:10.962
a name given to me
by the world's greatest doctor.

27:20.639 --> 27:23.932
And be

27:23.933 --> 27:26.019
gone!

27:31.900 --> 27:32.734
Huh?

27:44.287 --> 27:45.872
It's time you shut the hell up.

27:59.761 --> 28:01.054
Sanji!

28:05.767 --> 28:07.434
What? Get off me!

28:07.435 --> 28:09.436
What do you mean?
You're the one stuck to me!

28:09.437 --> 28:12.023
- Let go of my leg!
- Would you stay still for a second?

28:14.067 --> 28:16.736
It's the wrong leg, dumbass!

28:19.364 --> 28:21.407
- Not helping!
- Neither are you!

28:21.408 --> 28:23.075
Ah, your teamwork is pathetic!

28:23.076 --> 28:25.161
Unlike me and my partner.

28:30.208 --> 28:33.002
Oh shit.

28:34.212 --> 28:35.463
Aah!

28:41.553 --> 28:42.387
Ah.

28:46.099 --> 28:47.809
Now then.

28:57.861 --> 28:59.779
Party Table Kick Course!

29:10.081 --> 29:11.124
Aah!

29:19.924 --> 29:23.219
- Now that is what I call teamwork.
- Yeah.

29:24.387 --> 29:25.305
Yeah.

29:28.892 --> 29:30.392
- Um, guys?
- Nami.

29:30.393 --> 29:31.394
Nami!

29:38.401 --> 29:39.319
Aah!

29:39.903 --> 29:41.154
Aah!

29:53.750 --> 29:54.834
Go!

30:04.385 --> 30:06.054
Didn't know if you were coming back.

30:06.554 --> 30:08.931
The people of Drum
are the heart of this country,

30:08.932 --> 30:11.684
and I will not stop fighting
to protect them.

30:12.435 --> 30:14.938
Careful. You're starting
to sound like a leader.

30:36.876 --> 30:38.795
- It's the witch!
- Yeah.

30:40.296 --> 30:42.507
Now watch me work some magic.

30:49.722 --> 30:51.224
Luffy?

30:51.891 --> 30:53.100
Vivi!

30:53.101 --> 30:55.602
- Sanji! Nami! You missed it.
- Nami, you're okay!

30:55.603 --> 30:56.896
I'm glad you're okay.

30:58.523 --> 30:59.941
He defeated Wapol?

31:01.901 --> 31:03.862
Luffy, is that my coat?

31:05.238 --> 31:06.738
Is that Chopper?

31:06.739 --> 31:08.950
Whoa.

31:22.380 --> 31:24.298
How dare you?!

31:24.299 --> 31:28.302
Drum Kingdom is a member
of the World Government.

31:28.303 --> 31:31.180
Attacking me is an international crime!

31:31.764 --> 31:34.392
That kind of stuff
doesn't matter to a pirate.

31:35.143 --> 31:37.019
You'd know that if you really were one.

31:37.020 --> 31:39.897
Enough!

31:39.898 --> 31:43.401
I'm gonna blast you all to smithereens.

31:44.402 --> 31:48.323
Starting with that eyesore
of a pirate flag!

31:49.657 --> 31:51.117
No!

31:55.830 --> 31:56.831
Luffy.

32:01.044 --> 32:02.420
No.

32:05.465 --> 32:08.009
He's even dumber than I thought.

32:08.593 --> 32:11.053
Giving up his life

32:11.054 --> 32:16.392
for some silly,
meaningless scrap of fabric.

32:17.644 --> 32:19.395
Shows what you know,

32:20.104 --> 32:21.147
big mouth.

32:25.985 --> 32:28.279
The skull and crossbones
isn't flown lightly.

32:29.113 --> 32:30.823
It's an unbreakable symbol.

32:37.497 --> 32:40.457
A symbol… of conviction.

32:40.458 --> 32:41.751
But how?

32:42.460 --> 32:44.419
That was a direct hit!

32:44.420 --> 32:46.214
This flag

32:46.881 --> 32:48.841
isn't something to be mocked!

32:49.425 --> 32:50.718
Or shot at!

32:54.389 --> 32:57.100
Isn't that right, Chopper?

32:58.142 --> 32:59.143
That's right.

33:09.821 --> 33:12.490
Now stand back while I finish this guy.

33:20.123 --> 33:22.499
If a cannon won't kill you,

33:22.500 --> 33:25.628
I have other weapons I can use.

33:41.936 --> 33:43.479
So that's a pirate.

33:46.399 --> 33:48.067
There's no pirate like Luffy.

34:07.754 --> 34:10.465
Zoro! We can't hold them off much longer.

34:20.308 --> 34:21.517
We have to help him.

34:29.734 --> 34:30.568
I got you!

34:35.740 --> 34:38.076
Aah!

34:39.577 --> 34:40.912
Ah!

34:56.511 --> 34:57.637
Zoro!

34:58.221 --> 34:59.388
I'm out!

35:04.977 --> 35:08.272
I let him down in Loguetown.
Never again. Luffy!

35:12.735 --> 35:14.362
Gum Gum…

35:15.655 --> 35:18.032
- Air Assault!
- Air Assault!

35:48.396 --> 35:50.480
- Yeah!
- Hmm!

35:50.481 --> 35:53.067
That's my boy! Whoo!

35:55.903 --> 35:58.447
Luffy, you did it.

36:01.868 --> 36:02.743
Doctor…

36:05.163 --> 36:06.956
the kingdom is saved.

36:29.228 --> 36:30.271
We're gonna be okay.

36:31.272 --> 36:33.357
We're gonna be good, everybody.

36:35.693 --> 36:36.736
We got it.

36:37.778 --> 36:39.947
Classic Straw Hat situation right now.

36:46.495 --> 36:48.246
Someone's in good spirits.

36:48.247 --> 36:49.790
Keep it up.

36:50.333 --> 36:55.504
When we start working on those wounds,
well, you may not be smiling much longer.

37:14.190 --> 37:15.107
Is it over?

37:16.067 --> 37:17.485
Oh no.

37:18.110 --> 37:19.236
It's just beginning.

37:19.237 --> 37:21.154
Hey!

37:21.155 --> 37:23.365
Now let's get those chains off you.

37:23.366 --> 37:24.824
Tend to the injured.

37:24.825 --> 37:26.576
Put those skills to work.

37:26.577 --> 37:27.661
Now move!

37:27.662 --> 37:29.747
All right. Let's get to it.

37:44.845 --> 37:46.722
- Convenient, isn't it?
- Mmm.

37:47.223 --> 37:50.141
I could've climbed it. I was
actually looking forward to climbing it.

37:50.142 --> 37:53.479
I'm a bit of a mountain goat,
the way I navigate a… mountain trail.

37:54.105 --> 37:55.021
Whoa.

37:55.022 --> 37:56.982
Usopp! Zoro!

37:56.983 --> 37:58.984
Hey, you guys made it!

37:58.985 --> 38:00.610
Thank goodness you're all all right.

38:00.611 --> 38:02.655
No big deal. Just fought some monsters.

38:03.281 --> 38:04.323
Where's Nami?

38:06.284 --> 38:07.951
Nami, you're okay!

38:07.952 --> 38:09.161
Yeah, I'm fine.

38:10.121 --> 38:12.080
Finally, I don't feel like death anymore.

38:12.081 --> 38:13.249
You're welcome.

38:14.625 --> 38:15.543
Is that my coat?

38:17.128 --> 38:18.211
Add it to my bill.

38:18.212 --> 38:21.173
What kept you? What were you guys
doing up here all this time?

38:25.011 --> 38:26.429
Kicking the king's butt.

38:28.723 --> 38:30.557
That young man defeated Wapol?

38:30.558 --> 38:31.850
Well, I'll be damned.

38:31.851 --> 38:33.685
What of his two lieutenants?

38:33.686 --> 38:35.437
Sanji and Chopper took care of them.

38:35.438 --> 38:36.981
Piece of cake, to be honest.

38:39.400 --> 38:40.276
Who's Chopper?

38:42.403 --> 38:43.361
Him!

38:43.362 --> 38:45.156
Uh… uh…

38:47.283 --> 38:48.159
Whoa!

38:50.703 --> 38:52.121
It's Hiriluk's son.

38:55.583 --> 38:56.709
Mm-mm.

39:04.842 --> 39:06.052
Thank you.

39:08.512 --> 39:09.638
All of you.

39:11.432 --> 39:13.267
Because you fought for us,

39:13.934 --> 39:15.811
this kingdom can be born again.

39:26.197 --> 39:28.824
Consider your bill paid in full.

39:38.084 --> 39:40.836
The people will have their leader.

39:46.384 --> 39:47.510
Come on out, reindeer.

39:48.260 --> 39:49.220
Come with us.

39:50.471 --> 39:52.723
What? What do you mean?

39:53.307 --> 39:55.059
Let's go be pirates together.

39:59.397 --> 40:01.816
I would love to be a pirate with you all,

40:02.316 --> 40:03.817
but I can't.

40:03.818 --> 40:05.694
What do you mean "can't"?

40:06.320 --> 40:07.904
You saved my life.

40:07.905 --> 40:11.908
We're going to need a doctor,
given how much trouble we get into.

40:11.909 --> 40:15.870
Your transformations are so cool. They'll
be really useful in the battles to come.

40:15.871 --> 40:16.872
Stop!

40:21.752 --> 40:23.337
I'm very grateful to you all

40:23.921 --> 40:27.842
for being so nice to me
and everything you've done, but

40:28.509 --> 40:30.260
I'm a reindeer.

40:30.261 --> 40:33.596
I have hooves and antlers and a blue nose.

40:33.597 --> 40:35.390
I'm not a human like the rest of you.

40:35.391 --> 40:38.685
I could never be part of your group.
It's impossible! It's--

40:38.686 --> 40:43.649
Just shut up and come with us!

40:46.444 --> 40:47.653
That'll get him to join.

41:03.294 --> 41:05.671
Okay. I'll join you.

41:06.672 --> 41:10.676
Yeah!

41:11.510 --> 41:15.473
I'll meet you outside.
There's something I have to do first.

41:28.903 --> 41:29.987
Doctorine!

41:33.657 --> 41:35.867
I need to talk to you.

41:35.868 --> 41:38.621
Finally, my assistant shows up.

41:39.163 --> 41:40.998
You sure did a number around here.

41:41.624 --> 41:45.294
You're gonna be out foraging
to replace any medicine you damaged.

41:45.794 --> 41:48.339
Doctorine, I'm leaving.

41:49.507 --> 41:53.343
Well, yeah. I just told you that
you're going to be out foraging for any--

41:53.344 --> 41:54.803
I'm leaving with them.

41:57.348 --> 42:00.976
I'm gonna be their ship's doctor
and sail around the world with them.

42:06.065 --> 42:08.526
You ungrateful little shit.

42:10.110 --> 42:12.029
After all I've done for you…

42:13.197 --> 42:14.532
Given you a home,

42:15.241 --> 42:16.492
taught you medicine.

42:17.326 --> 42:19.994
And I'm very grateful for all you've done.

42:19.995 --> 42:22.121
But I have to chase my dreams.

42:22.122 --> 42:23.624
You?

42:24.208 --> 42:27.836
A little crybaby reindeer
is gonna be a pirate?

42:29.004 --> 42:31.715
You will never survive out on the seas.

42:34.385 --> 42:36.135
That may be true about me,

42:36.136 --> 42:39.222
but I'm also a man,
and I have dreams of my own.

42:39.223 --> 42:42.350
And I won't be sailing alone.
I have my friends.

42:42.351 --> 42:45.020
You… you can't stop me!

42:45.521 --> 42:49.524
So you're gonna leave
to follow your silly little dreams.

42:49.525 --> 42:51.359
Just like that old quack.

42:51.360 --> 42:54.029
You're gonna end up just like him.

42:56.407 --> 42:57.992
Come back here!

43:02.454 --> 43:04.372
- Oh!
- Whoo!

43:04.373 --> 43:06.374
Here I come! Here I come!

43:06.375 --> 43:07.750
What's taking him so long?

43:07.751 --> 43:09.002
Okay, my turn.

43:09.003 --> 43:10.546
Can't be easy, you know?

43:11.130 --> 43:12.673
Leaving home for the first time.

43:14.133 --> 43:17.303
Oh!

43:18.804 --> 43:21.515
Oh!

43:22.933 --> 43:24.643
Whoo!

43:27.021 --> 43:28.022
What is that?

43:36.655 --> 43:37.698
Whoa.

43:44.538 --> 43:47.499
Everybody, get in. We're going
down the mountain and out to sea!

43:48.709 --> 43:50.502
Another Chopper?!

43:51.003 --> 43:53.212
I get the back seat!

43:53.213 --> 43:55.799
Ooh-ee!

44:24.161 --> 44:24.995
Luffy!

44:33.170 --> 44:34.505
Aah!

44:52.064 --> 44:53.232
Whoa.

44:57.861 --> 44:59.530
Welcome aboard, Doctor.

45:00.989 --> 45:03.200
My very first pirate ship.

45:03.826 --> 45:06.370
Come on! Come on! It's time to head off!

45:06.870 --> 45:08.664
Let's go!

45:29.601 --> 45:30.686
Hmm.

45:36.066 --> 45:37.651
I know what it feels like.

45:39.236 --> 45:40.279
Leaving home.

45:43.824 --> 45:45.617
But you don't have to be nervous.

45:48.078 --> 45:49.413
You're a Straw Hat now.

45:51.206 --> 45:52.123
Hmm.

45:52.124 --> 45:53.834
The Going Merry is your home.

45:55.502 --> 45:56.879
And we got your back.

45:58.547 --> 45:59.590
Always.

46:02.801 --> 46:06.262
Oh crap! I left my backpack
with all my supplies behind.

46:06.263 --> 46:07.347
You mean this?

46:11.894 --> 46:13.561
It was on the sleigh.

46:13.562 --> 46:15.522
But I didn't…

46:18.400 --> 46:20.319
Doctorine.

46:21.361 --> 46:22.738
She must've known.

46:24.490 --> 46:25.657
Mmm.

46:36.043 --> 46:37.461
What are those?

46:39.379 --> 46:40.839
It's a secret.

46:47.846 --> 46:49.097
You found what I need.

46:52.810 --> 46:54.311
Found one in the armory.

46:56.647 --> 46:58.022
What do you need this for?

46:58.023 --> 47:00.526
I don't like tearful goodbyes.

47:03.654 --> 47:07.449
Hiriluk had a very particular idea
of how to cure this country.

47:08.617 --> 47:10.702
In the end, he figured out how,

47:11.495 --> 47:13.747
but he never got to do it himself.

47:18.418 --> 47:19.294
Raise it up.

47:28.804 --> 47:30.180
Doctor, what is this?

47:31.014 --> 47:31.890
Just watch.

47:40.107 --> 47:42.109
Let's find out if he was right.

48:24.359 --> 48:26.612
It's so… beautiful.

48:29.656 --> 48:32.326
It's snow, but… it looks like…

48:33.285 --> 48:35.329
Cherry blossoms.

48:40.667 --> 48:42.669
Turn on the spotlights.

48:45.714 --> 48:48.926
<i>Once people lose hope,
they give in to fear.</i>

48:49.801 --> 48:53.263
<i>We need to give them their hope back.</i>

48:55.474 --> 49:00.895
<i>The powerful emotion
he experienced from looking</i>

49:00.896 --> 49:03.106
at cherry blossoms

49:04.107 --> 49:05.400
had healed him.

49:12.991 --> 49:15.327
<i>Nothing is impossible.</i>

49:16.036 --> 49:19.623
<i>We never, ever give up.</i>

50:18.056 --> 50:20.767
Go on, you foolish boy.

50:24.771 --> 50:28.400
If a man can bring cherry blossoms
to this frozen land,

50:28.942 --> 50:31.361
then maybe a reindeer can be a pirate.

50:33.280 --> 50:35.365
What wonder fools are capable of.

50:36.366 --> 50:38.785
It's fools that have saved this place.

50:39.453 --> 50:41.329
Not just Dr. Hiriluk.

50:44.124 --> 50:46.460
Monkey D. Luffy.

50:47.377 --> 50:49.046
He is a special young man.

50:50.172 --> 50:52.924
Perhaps he will be the one
to find the One Piece.

50:56.053 --> 50:59.014
He does share certain traits with

50:59.514 --> 51:01.140
Gol D. Roger.

51:01.141 --> 51:02.434
Gol D.?

51:03.727 --> 51:05.270
You mean Gold Roger.

51:08.065 --> 51:10.525
Is that what he's known by these days?

51:12.569 --> 51:17.866
Our reindeer has hitched his wagon
to a very interesting one indeed.

51:18.784 --> 51:21.870
The Will of D. lives on.

51:23.205 --> 51:24.623
Cheers.

51:37.052 --> 51:38.261
All right, everyone.

51:39.679 --> 51:43.683
Let's give a warm welcome
to our new ship's doctor.

51:44.184 --> 51:46.103
Tony Tony Chopper!

51:54.820 --> 51:56.822
Chopper!

52:03.036 --> 52:04.871
Chopper, Chopper, check this out!

52:05.372 --> 52:07.164
Yeah!

52:07.165 --> 52:08.959
Aah!

52:18.468 --> 52:20.136
Still got that dinosaur I killed?

52:20.137 --> 52:22.180
I never had one,
seeing as you never killed any.

52:24.683 --> 52:27.101
Yeah!

52:27.102 --> 52:29.604
This is the most fun I've ever had.

52:31.106 --> 52:32.858
Can I try the knife thing?

52:35.235 --> 52:38.737
Too much for you? I thought
you'd be used to our antics by now.

52:38.738 --> 52:40.406
No, no, it's just…

52:40.407 --> 52:42.616
- Want a beer?
- I prefer hot chocolate.

52:42.617 --> 52:43.451
I'm gonna miss this.

52:44.119 --> 52:45.162
Miss this?

52:45.996 --> 52:47.038
Where are you going?

52:48.248 --> 52:52.002
Well, when we get to Alabasta,
we'll be going our separate ways.

52:52.669 --> 52:55.963
You'll drop me off
and continue on towards the One Piece.

52:55.964 --> 52:56.798
Yeah.

52:57.716 --> 52:59.634
We <i>are</i> going to find the One Piece.

53:02.512 --> 53:05.681
But not until after we help you
defeat those Baroque Works guys

53:05.682 --> 53:07.309
and save your kingdom.

53:15.400 --> 53:16.902
You'd really do that?

53:17.944 --> 53:19.863
Did you think
we were just gonna leave you?

53:21.072 --> 53:24.576
Like I said, I thought
you'd be used to our antics by now.

53:25.076 --> 53:27.662
You're one of us too.

53:28.830 --> 53:30.874
And friends help each other.

53:32.042 --> 53:33.084
Dummy.

53:37.047 --> 53:38.673
I never should've doubted it.

53:40.592 --> 53:42.510
I appreciate you all.

53:51.311 --> 53:54.230
If you're going to help me,
there's something you need to know.

53:54.231 --> 53:59.361
What I went undercover to find out,
and what Igaram lost his life to discover.

54:00.445 --> 54:02.488
<i>Is that how you speak to your superior?</i>

54:02.489 --> 54:04.823
<i>My apologies, Mr. 0.</i>

54:04.824 --> 54:07.410
<i>The Marines have become aware
of our movements.</i>

54:08.036 --> 54:11.456
<i>Dispatch the Unluckies. Clean up the mess.</i>

54:13.083 --> 54:14.709
<i>The Straw Hat Pirates</i>

54:15.502 --> 54:16.962
<i>taking Princess Vivi…</i>

54:21.132 --> 54:24.051
Vivi, the missing princess of Alabasta.

54:24.052 --> 54:26.012
I recognize one of those voices.

54:26.596 --> 54:27.639
A Straw Hat.

54:29.099 --> 54:32.434
- But the other--
- Mr. 0. He's the leader of Baroque Works.

54:32.435 --> 54:35.354
We uncovered
their most closely guarded secret.

54:35.355 --> 54:37.482
Mr. 0's true identity.

54:37.983 --> 54:41.861
To even know this recording existed,
Mr. 0 must be someone with information.

54:42.362 --> 54:43.279
Connections.

54:43.280 --> 54:46.324
And Garp doesn't want Mr. 0's identity
known until he has proof.

54:47.742 --> 54:50.661
Even the accusation could rock
the foundations of the Marines.

54:50.662 --> 54:53.956
If we are going to take this fight
to Baroque Works,

54:53.957 --> 54:56.375
you'll need to know
who you're truly up against.

54:56.376 --> 54:57.585
<i>Baroque Works,</i>

54:58.086 --> 54:59.004
<i>Straw Hats…</i>

55:00.797 --> 55:02.507
<i>Everything's pointing to Alabasta.</i>

55:05.010 --> 55:06.177
So that's where we're going.

55:11.933 --> 55:14.601
Mr. 11 and Miss Thursday
confirmed the destruction

55:14.602 --> 55:16.312
of the intercepted transmission.

55:16.313 --> 55:21.025
Good. Any update
as to the identity of this Mr. Prince?

55:21.026 --> 55:22.152
Not yet.

55:22.861 --> 55:24.029
We'll find him.

55:25.238 --> 55:27.072
And what of the good King Wapol?

55:27.073 --> 55:28.283
Out of the picture.

55:29.659 --> 55:32.746
Even with your generous gift, he failed.

55:35.582 --> 55:37.125
We got what we needed from him.

55:38.126 --> 55:42.255
His royal treasury will go a long way
towards furthering our cause.

55:42.797 --> 55:44.966
Don't you mean <i>your</i> cause?

55:55.018 --> 55:56.269
Come now.

55:56.770 --> 55:58.395
What's good for me

55:58.396 --> 55:59.856
is good for you.

56:02.609 --> 56:03.943
For all of us.

56:05.403 --> 56:08.113
I've called the officer agents
to gather in Alabasta.

56:08.114 --> 56:10.532
They should prove more effective
than the others.

56:10.533 --> 56:14.329
I'm getting tired
of cleaning up lower agents' messes.

56:15.663 --> 56:18.541
Ever so droll, Nico Robin.

56:23.880 --> 56:25.548
I've told you not to call me by that name.

56:28.510 --> 56:29.469
Relax.

56:30.678 --> 56:34.265
Everything we've worked for
will soon come to fruition.

56:35.683 --> 56:39.104
We commence with Operation Utopia.

56:39.771 --> 56:41.398
Alabasta will fall.

56:42.899 --> 56:46.319
And I will come one step closer

56:47.821 --> 56:49.906
to obtaining the One Piece.

57:08.633 --> 57:13.470
<i>I braved through the frost
Of the vast unknown</i>

57:13.471 --> 57:18.267
<i>I kept my heart safe
On a glacier's throne</i>

57:18.268 --> 57:23.147
<i>The forest's my friend
And the cold's my cloak</i>

57:23.148 --> 57:27.860
<i>I wandered a monster, I walked alone</i>

57:27.861 --> 57:32.739
<i>You carved me a name
From the silent wind</i>

57:32.740 --> 57:37.119
